commitResults.messageBody:
One Command may have many different alias. Currently, to add more
alias to a command, we have to add more COMMAND_WORD in each
command class. This will lead to more switch case in AddressBookParser
and this is not scalable in the future if there were to be many more
aliases added.

Refactoring all the COMMAND_WORD in the different command into one
enum CommandWord allows us consolidates all the COMMAND_WORD for
different Command. The use of enum also removes the need for adding
more switch case everytime a new alias is added. We just have to add
the alias in the enum and the switch block in AddressBookParser will
still work.

commitResults.messageTitle: Edit PersonModuleCodesContainsKeywordsPredicts to improve find by module codes
commitResults.messageBody:
For a find command using module codes, all module codes in the search query
must be matched for the person to be matched.

For example,
* Person A has module `CS2100`
* Person B has modules `CS2100` `CS2103T`
* Person C has modules `CS2100` `CS2103T` `CS2106`

Searching with command `find m/CS2100 m/CS2103T` will only return persons B and C

commitResults.messageTitle: Parse for names using prefix n/
commitResults.messageBody:
Find command now parses for names using prefix n/
Able to parse and search for multiple names

Currently, to find input multiple keywords for find, user has to do the following:
* find n/alice n/bob
or
* find m/cs2100 m/CS2103T

To make it faster and easier to find, contHACKS now accepts multiple keyword search with a single prefix:
* find n/alice bob
or
* find m/cs2100 CS2103T

This works as system does not allow for multiple prefixes in a single search
